<h2>Key points</h2><ul><li>Ptosis is when your child has a droopy eyelid or eyelids.</li><li>Ptosis is usually caused by a weakness of the muscle that lifts the upper eyelid.</li><li>Your child's eye doctor will discuss if and which surgery is best for your child.</li></ul>
